The paper presents a fast algorithm for kernel summation problems, which are commonly used in computational physics, numerical approximation, non-parametric statistics, and machine learning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), and Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-categories.
